Paper: hep-th/0301179

Date: 2003-01-23

Title: Rolling down to D-brane and tachyon matter

Authors: Akira Ishida, Shozo Uehara

Comments: 8 pages, references added, solution corrected, revised and extended

Journal-ref: JHEP 0302 (2003) 050

We investigate the spatially inhomogeneous decay of an unstable D-brane andconstruct an asymptotic solution which describes a codimension one D-brane andthe tachyon matter in boundary string field theory. In this solution, thetachyon matter exists around the lower-dimensional D-brane.